1
00:01:30,820 --> 00:01:34,990
[Dream of Golden Years]

2
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:36,430
Our company's second-quarter

3
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:39,380
[2015]

4
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:37,310
top seller

5
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:39,039
is our new colleague,

6
00:01:39,229 --> 00:01:39,960
Xia Xiaolan.

7
00:01:41,950 --> 00:01:43,640
Here's the certificate and bonus.

8
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,400
Keep up the good work.

9
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,000
Thank you.

10
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:45,590
Everyone should

11
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:47,000
learn from Xia Xiaolan in the future

12
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:47,920
and create more value

13
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,580
and benefits for our company.

14
00:01:50,229 --> 00:01:51,490
Liu, come to my office.

15
00:01:51,610 --> 00:01:54,200
[Ms. Xiaolan won the Top Seller title
in the Business Group's Q2 2015 sales ranking.]

16
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,150
Anyone who gets her clients

17
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:55,680
could become the top seller,

18
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,200
right?

19
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,200
Don't try to deny it.

20
00:01:58,710 --> 00:01:59,350
She goes

21
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:01,070
to Mr. Gu's office every day.

22
00:02:01,170 --> 00:02:01,890
Who knows

23
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,980
what kind of relationship they have?

24
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:16,400
How do rumors start?

25
00:02:17,079 --> 00:02:18,120
Is it because of jealousy

26
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:18,980
or just for fun—

27
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:21,200
It is often impossible to know.

28
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:22,910
But I know it.

29
00:02:23,870 --> 00:02:25,670
Running away won't stop rumors.

30
00:02:26,310 --> 00:02:27,079
Backing down

31
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:30,000
will only be seen
as an admission of guilt.

32
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,800
People will embellish the story

33
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,090
with vivid details.

34
00:02:34,210 --> 00:02:38,370
[Episode 2: Rumors That Grew Wings]

35
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:40,680
Come here.

36
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,150
You think we don't know
who you really are?

37
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:42,750
Let me go!

38
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:43,800
Help!

39
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:44,520
Weren't you getting along

40
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,590
well with Zhang Erlai?

41
00:02:45,590 --> 00:02:46,120
Let me go!

42
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,710
Why are you pretending to be pure?

43
00:02:47,710 --> 00:02:49,630
Everyone knows you're Xia Xiaolan

44
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:51,760
from Dahe Village, who sleeps around.

45
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:01,160
Are you okay?

46
00:03:05,030 --> 00:03:06,560
You guys are really something—

47
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,310
bullying a girl in broad daylight.

48
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:08,910
Get him!

49
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,140
Come on.

50
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:25,630
Excuse me.

51
00:03:25,630 --> 00:03:26,360
Move aside.

52
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:28,600
Does it hurt?

53
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:29,430
Yes.

54
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:31,430
Want to keep fighting?

55
00:03:31,430 --> 00:03:31,870
No.

56
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:32,590
No. No.

57
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:33,150
Stop it!

58
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,430
What's going on here?

59
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:36,000
Officer.

60
00:03:36,110 --> 00:03:36,870
It's them.

61
00:03:38,430 --> 00:03:39,230
Take them all.

62
00:03:39,470 --> 00:03:39,960
Get up.

63
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:40,520
Come on.

64
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,800
Get up. Get up.

65
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:42,570
Easy, easy.

66
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:43,450
-Ouch.
-Get up.

67
00:03:45,130 --> 00:03:45,750
And you two,

68
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:47,280
come with us to the station.

69
00:03:47,590 --> 00:03:48,400
Cheng, are you okay?

70
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:48,930
I'm fine.

71
00:03:56,410 --> 00:03:57,340
Are you alright?

72
00:04:05,660 --> 00:04:07,270
Alright,
we've understood the situation already.

73
00:04:07,270 --> 00:04:08,130
You can go back.

74
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:10,400
Miss,
when walking alone on remote paths,

75
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,790
you should be more careful.

76
00:04:11,790 --> 00:04:13,470
Xia Xiaolan is just a loose woman,

77
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:14,750
not some good girl.

78
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:15,750
Shut up.

79
00:04:17,709 --> 00:04:18,910
Okay, you can go back.

80
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:19,820
Thank you.

81
00:04:19,820 --> 00:04:20,420
Thank you.

82
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:24,430
Thank you so much.

83
00:04:24,830 --> 00:04:25,760
That's alright.

84
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:28,270
Do you have somewhere else to go?

85
00:04:30,590 --> 00:04:31,120
Yes.

86
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:41,710
Miss.

87
00:04:42,430 --> 00:04:43,830
What are you looking for?

88
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:44,920
Is it a wall clock

89
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,190
or a wristwatch?

90
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,120
Alarm clock.

91
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:48,159
Do you have an alarm clock?

92
00:04:48,159 --> 00:04:49,560
Yes, yes. Look over here.

93
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:57,150
There aren't any
with cartoon prints here.

94
00:04:57,390 --> 00:04:59,320
This is the only one with a pattern.

95
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:01,890
Let me see this one.

96
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,480
Sure.

97
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:05,900
Take a look.

98
00:05:08,030 --> 00:05:09,030
Are you buying it?

99
00:05:09,190 --> 00:05:11,190
Don't touch it if you're not buying.

100
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:12,800
Okay.

101
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,060
I'll take this one.

102
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:24,610
Have you got it?

103
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,630
You helped me today.

104
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:27,230
Thank you.

105
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:28,440
That's alright.

106
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,920
My name is Zhou Cheng.

107
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,000
I am a high school graduate.

108
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,680
I'll start working in two months.

109
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,870
I've been free lately,

110
00:05:33,870 --> 00:05:35,100
so I've been doing some transport work.

111
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:36,030
But don't worry.

112
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:37,480
It's legitimate work.

113
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:39,210
I just make a small profit.

114
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:40,600
Now,

115
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:42,880
may I get to know you?

116
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,060
My name is Xia Xiaolan.

117
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,680
As for anything else,

118
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,240
I don't know, either.

119
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,690
You're quite interesting,

120
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,659
not even knowing about yourself.

121
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:58,480
Xia Xiaolan.

122
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,450
Xia Xiaolan!

123
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,630
Ms. Xiaolan.

124
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,560
Ms. Xiaolan.

125
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:10,770
Ms. Xiaolan.

126
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:15,890
Ms. Xiaolan.

127
00:06:17,830 --> 00:06:19,040
You're finally awake.

128
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,970
You just fainted from heatstroke.

129
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:21,640
Here.

130
00:06:23,770 --> 00:06:24,800
This is my own water bottle.

131
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:25,580
I've washed it three times.

132
00:06:25,580 --> 00:06:26,510
It's very clean.

133
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,390
Have some water to recover.

134
00:06:28,390 --> 00:06:28,720
Here.

135
00:06:34,510 --> 00:06:35,600
You are...

136
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Wang...

137
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:39,560
Wang Jianhua.

138
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:41,270
I'm from Beijing,

139
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,159
responsible for promoting

140
00:06:42,159 --> 00:06:44,420
our agricultural planting techniques.

141
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,210
I don't understand any of that.

142
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,800
So you're just someone

143
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,200
who farms with us, right?

144
00:06:50,890 --> 00:06:52,330
Right, that's not wrong.

145
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:53,800
Thank you.

146
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,360
Take it easy.

147
00:07:01,070 --> 00:07:02,400
That's enough. Thanks.

148
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,070
No, no.

149
00:07:03,630 --> 00:07:04,750
Your heatstroke was serious.

150
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:06,350
You should rest a bit longer.

151
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:08,680
Everyone, stop crowding around.

152
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,610
Get back to work.

153
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,380
Have another sip of water.

154
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:14,490
Drink some more.

155
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:15,960
Thank you.

156
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,820
Where am I?

157
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:33,780
Don't move.

158
00:07:33,830 --> 00:07:35,030
You're still on an IV.

159
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,040
Did I fall asleep?

160
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:42,600
Yes.

161
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,460
You seemed to be dreaming.

162
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,070
You were smiling in your sleep.

163
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:47,930
Just like this.

164
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:52,200
Everyone else has dreams

165
00:07:52,390 --> 00:07:53,830
with happy and joyful smiles.

166
00:07:53,830 --> 00:07:56,490
Why did it seem like
you were mocking something?

167
00:07:58,159 --> 00:07:59,070
I dreamed of

168
00:07:59,070 --> 00:08:00,630
a hasty love story.

169
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,430
You know, people

170
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:04,430
are really interesting sometimes.

171
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:06,850
They meet someone a few times,

172
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,430
get a little bit of care,

173
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:12,040
and then they want to spend
the rest of their lives with them.

174
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,720
This standard for choosing a partner

175
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,000
is really quite low.

176
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,310
So,

177
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:22,120
you don't believe in love at first sight.

178
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,380
How can you fall in love

179
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:25,310
when you know nothing about them?

180
00:08:25,310 --> 00:08:27,370
What if the attraction at first sight

181
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,120
is strong enough?

182
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,240
What attraction—

183
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,200
strong enough

184
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:36,120
to suck my blood?

185
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,860
Nurse, please remove the IV here.

186
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:41,600
Okay, coming.

187
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:47,550
Press here.

188
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:50,480
Okay.

189
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:53,350
Thank you.

190
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,550
Take it easy.

191
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:56,550
Come.

192
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:03,120
Um,

193
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:05,010
let me take you home later.

194
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,320
Don't refuse yet.

195
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,240
If you insist

196
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,370
on going back alone,

197
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:11,310
I'll still insist on taking you.

198
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,270
Warm,

199
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,200
considerate,

200
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,030
knows his boundaries—

201
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:16,790
This boy

202
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:18,320
actually matches my taste.

203
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:20,390
But I don't believe a man's feelings

204
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:22,320
can stay focused on just one woman,

205
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,000
especially when she's

206
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,320
over 10 years older than him

207
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,920
and from another dimension.

208
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:29,560
Thank you.

209
00:09:37,150 --> 00:09:38,480
What kind of trash

210
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,000
is gossiping
about other people's business,

211
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:40,480
saying—

212
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:42,510
Fen.

213
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,450
Go ahead with your work.

214
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,220
What happened?

215
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:50,510
Just now, on my way here,

216
00:09:50,510 --> 00:09:52,170
I overheard two people saying

217
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:53,390
that our Xiaolan

218
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,750
was bullied in town.

219
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:56,960
They even called her a loose woman.

220
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:57,760
Who said that?

221
00:09:59,150 --> 00:10:00,600
I chewed them both out.

222
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:02,440
Don't worry.

223
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,480
As long as I'm around,

224
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,870
no one in the village will dare
to gossip anymore.

225
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:06,550
However,

226
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,380
I can't control what happens elsewhere.

227
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:09,710
Alright, I understand.

228
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,080
You should

229
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,550
go check on Fen first.

230
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:13,480
I'll go meet Xiaolan.

231
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:13,810
Okay.

232
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:24,240
Just turn the corner ahead
and we're there.

233
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:24,840
Thank you.

234
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,050
That's alright.

235
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:30,040
Thank you.

236
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:30,960
Cheng,

237
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:32,670
I'll sort the goods.

238
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:33,400
You two talk.

239
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:40,910
Wei and I

240
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:42,720
are staying at the Anqing Guesthouse.

241
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,360
If you're going

242
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:44,720
to the town again tomorrow,

243
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:46,250
you can ask us to go with you.

244
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,150
No need.

245
00:10:47,390 --> 00:10:47,910
Thanks.

246
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:48,650
Gotta go.

247
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,320
Thank you.

248
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:17,370
Xiaolan!

249
00:11:24,630 --> 00:11:25,320
Who are you?

250
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,660
Why are you following her?

251
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,480
Hello, I'm Zhou Cheng,

252
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,440
and I'm the delivery person.

253
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,510
He helped me today.

254
00:11:38,270 --> 00:11:39,470
Well, thank you then.

255
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:42,150
You should go back and rest early.

256
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:43,210
I'll be going then.

257
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:50,290
Where are you staying?

258
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:53,750
I'm staying at the town guesthouse.

259
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,720
I happen to be going
to the town tomorrow.

260
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,180
I'll bring you breakfast.

261
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,080
And for lunch,

262
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:00,810
I'll treat you to a meal in town—

263
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:01,870
as thanks

264
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,040
from Xiaolan.

265
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,100
Go back now.

266
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:07,680
Thank you.

267
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:14,960
Cheng.

268
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:16,000
Who was that guy just now?

269
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,130
He seemed so fierce.

270
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:19,230
Probably her father.

271
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:20,960
Let's go.

272
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:21,890
Let's go.

273
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:26,130
He helped you.

274
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,860
We should thank him properly.

275
00:12:28,270 --> 00:12:29,670
Homemade food

276
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:30,790
shows sincerity.

277
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:32,930
Tomorrow morning,

278
00:12:33,630 --> 00:12:35,630
I'll go to the police station in town

279
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:37,360
to ask about today's incident.

280
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:38,750
And I'll also check

281
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,580
if they're decent people.

282
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:44,910
Thank...

283
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:46,670
Thank you.

284
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:48,600
Kid...

285
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,390
What are you thanking me for?

286
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:51,190
We're family.

287
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:01,030
Those two are city folks.

288
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:03,000
I wonder

289
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:03,910
if they will like

290
00:13:03,910 --> 00:13:04,960
these sour radish and pork dumplings.

291
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,000
They've probably never had them before.

292
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,530
Let them try something new.

293
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:10,200
Cook their dumplings

294
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,260
tomorrow morning.

295
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:12,130
Alright.

296
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,670
It's the New Year! Time to eat dumplings!

297
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:16,790
Now we can have them
even when it's not the New Year.

298
00:13:16,790 --> 00:13:17,850
Life is better now.

299
00:13:18,870 --> 00:13:19,600
Thank you...

300
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:22,090
Thank you so much for your trouble.

301
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,200
Xiaolan, it's no trouble at all.

302
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,070
We're making them for ourselves, too.

303
00:13:26,070 --> 00:13:27,120
Oh right, I remember

304
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,630
you make the prettiest dumplings.

305
00:13:28,630 --> 00:13:29,440
You should

306
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,030
make their dumplings.

307
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:30,440
Yes.

308
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:30,940
Come on.

309
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:31,720
Yes.

310
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,890
Xiaolan makes the best dumplings.

311
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:35,240
Come on.

312
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:36,320
Wrap one.

313
00:13:36,410 --> 00:13:37,680
I don't know how.

314
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:41,480
The first batch is ready. Here.

315
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,450
Try them and see how they taste.

316
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:44,790
Try them quickly.

317
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,530
Tao, let Xiaolan eat first.

318
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,320
It's okay.

319
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:48,310
Tao, go ahead.

320
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,250
Thank you, Xiaolan.

321
00:13:50,290 --> 00:13:51,070
Hurry up.

322
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,320
Be careful. It's hot.

323
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,480
How does it taste?

324
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,870
Even though the alarm clocks
are different,

325
00:14:02,870 --> 00:14:04,550
sincerity makes all the difference.

326
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:05,960
Please, let me go back.

327
00:14:56,910 --> 00:14:57,600
Xiaolan.

328
00:14:58,550 --> 00:15:00,210
You set an alarm at night, too?

329
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:05,600
I was just trying it out.

330
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,240
Alright.

331
00:15:06,630 --> 00:15:08,150
Try it. Try it.

332
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,030
Lan.

333
00:15:27,790 --> 00:15:29,250
Is the alarm clock broken?

334
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,620
Let me get you a new one.

335
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:32,320
It's fine.

336
00:15:32,790 --> 00:15:33,270
No need.

337
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:51,940
What...

338
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:53,510
What are you going to say?

339
00:15:53,510 --> 00:15:54,740
No… nothing.

340
00:15:55,150 --> 00:15:55,550
I...

341
00:15:56,150 --> 00:15:57,480
I'll get you some water.

342
00:16:05,790 --> 00:16:07,080
Useless thing.

343
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,380
Stop making noise.

344
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,600
What's wrong with Xiaolan?

345
00:16:28,870 --> 00:16:30,390
She's probably testing the alarm clock

346
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:31,550
to see if it works.

347
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,840
Why do we need alarm clocks here?

348
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,840
When the sun rises and the roosters crow,

349
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,840
everyone gets up.

350
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,120
Whenever she wants to wake up,

351
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:39,270
we can call her.

352
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:40,750
Maybe

353
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:42,600
she's afraid of troubling you.

354
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:44,910
Fen.

355
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,150
Have you noticed

356
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,640
that since Xiaolan hit her head,

357
00:16:48,670 --> 00:16:50,320
she seems different from before?

358
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:51,960
Look, she doesn't eat vinegar,

359
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,420
doesn't drink spicy soup,

360
00:16:53,570 --> 00:16:55,210
can't even make dumplings,

361
00:16:55,630 --> 00:16:57,480
and she's so polite with us,

362
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:59,590
like she's become someone else.

363
00:17:00,030 --> 00:17:00,720
Later,

364
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:01,840
you should take her

365
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,570
to the big hospital in the city.

366
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,500
What's wrong with you?

367
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,750
Are you crying again?

368
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,200
It's nothing.

369
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:41,310
I'm just happy to see

370
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:42,720
you doing so well.

371
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:45,240
Don't worry.

372
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:47,830
I'm not the same Xia Xiaolan as before.

373
00:17:47,830 --> 00:17:49,760
I won't do foolish things anymore.

374
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:55,350
I know.

375
00:17:57,590 --> 00:17:58,240
Xiaolan.

376
00:17:59,590 --> 00:18:00,480
Today I collected

377
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:02,080
two big baskets of duck eggs.

378
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:03,790
What?

379
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:06,110
Didn't you tell me

380
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:07,710
to collect duck eggs at home?

381
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:09,640
At first,

382
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:11,030
I didn't have much of a plan.

383
00:18:11,030 --> 00:18:12,030
Then I suddenly remembered

384
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:12,830
what you said,

385
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:14,610
"Just look for kids Tao's age."

386
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,530
One minute, one kid would pop up here,

387
00:18:16,530 --> 00:18:17,160
holding one.

388
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:18,240
The next minute,
another would pop up there,

389
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:18,970
holding two.

390
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,400
In just one afternoon,

391
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,400
I collected two big baskets of duck eggs.

392
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:22,960
Tomorrow I'll go with you

393
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:24,030
to sell the eggs.

394
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:26,680
No need.

395
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:28,920
I'll go by myself tomorrow.

396
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,250
You should rest at home.

397
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:33,970
Alright.

398
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:35,510
Your uncle will

399
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:36,570
go with you anyway.

400
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:39,510
I'll stay home and collect eggs.

401
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:43,310
Although

402
00:18:43,790 --> 00:18:44,590
everything here

403
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:45,720
feels strange to me.

404
00:18:47,550 --> 00:18:48,880
This woman named Liu Fen

405
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:51,420
makes me want to get closer to her.

406
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:53,710
She is simple-minded

407
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:54,790
and weak,

408
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:57,440
but she gives her all

409
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,120
to love her daughter.

410
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:00,480
Xia Xiaolan.

411
00:19:01,550 --> 00:19:03,160
I actually envy you a little.

412
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:22,110
This kid

413
00:19:22,110 --> 00:19:24,110
is always playing
with new gadgets.

414
00:19:24,110 --> 00:19:25,440
This thing is loud.

415
00:19:47,510 --> 00:19:50,240
What time did I cross over?

416
00:19:52,330 --> 00:19:52,990
Afternoon.

417
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:53,880
Yes.

418
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:56,520
I'll try again in the afternoon.

419
00:19:58,070 --> 00:19:58,600
Brother.

420
00:19:59,240 --> 00:19:59,900
Dumplings.

421
00:20:00,030 --> 00:20:00,400
Okay.

422
00:20:00,510 --> 00:20:00,840
Here.

423
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:04,550
Xiaolan.

424
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:06,470
Hurry down. Let's go.

425
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:07,790
Let's deliver these dumplings.

426
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:08,270
Okay.

427
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,720
Here comes the noodles.

428
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:17,440
Thank you.

429
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:18,370
That's alright.

430
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:23,190
These dumplings are beautifully wrapped.

431
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:26,350
My family made them.

432
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:27,740
I'm not very good at it.

433
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:30,550
I actually know how.

434
00:20:30,550 --> 00:20:31,880
I'll show you sometime.

435
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:36,070
Wei was there yesterday.

436
00:20:36,070 --> 00:20:37,920
He went with your uncle
to the police station.

437
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,250
It will be handled well.

438
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:40,550
Thank you all.

439
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:41,750
Don't mention it.

440
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:46,750
What's in these dumplings?

441
00:20:46,750 --> 00:20:47,680
Pickled radish?

442
00:20:49,070 --> 00:20:49,670
It's good.

443
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:51,590
This way, it's not greasy at all.

444
00:20:52,830 --> 00:20:54,890
Your family must be well-off, right?

445
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:55,790
In these times,

446
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:57,790
everyone loves oily and meaty food,

447
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,590
but you don't like it.

448
00:21:00,790 --> 00:21:01,850
Yes, that's right.

449
00:21:02,510 --> 00:21:03,640
I did sports as a kid.

450
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,350
My family made me eat meat every day,

451
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:06,480
so I got tired of it.

452
00:21:06,550 --> 00:21:07,720
You did sports?

453
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,000
I trained in sprinting for a few years,

454
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,930
but then I got injured and stopped.

455
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:14,080
Although the injury wasn't serious,

456
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,210
I didn't really have

457
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,630
any interest in sports training,

458
00:21:16,630 --> 00:21:17,240
so I quit.

459
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:18,880
After quitting sports,

460
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:21,010
you could still go back to high school.

461
00:21:21,070 --> 00:21:22,470
Your grades must be good.

462
00:21:23,030 --> 00:21:24,030
I won't be modest.

463
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:25,560
They really were good.

464
00:21:33,510 --> 00:21:34,640
Are you trying to say

465
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:35,880
you envy me?

466
00:21:36,710 --> 00:21:37,840
Having a good family

467
00:21:38,270 --> 00:21:40,110
and being able to do whatever I want?

468
00:21:40,110 --> 00:21:41,770
It's actually not that great.

469
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:43,610
I've come to realize

470
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,240
that when life's easier,

471
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:46,640
people lose their drive.

472
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:47,880
Look at Wei and me.

473
00:21:48,270 --> 00:21:50,200
We seem capable of doing anything,

474
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:52,700
but we're not excellent at anything.

475
00:21:53,590 --> 00:21:54,160
Then

476
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:56,360
why don't you find something to pursue?

477
00:21:59,590 --> 00:22:00,990
I haven't figured it out.

478
00:22:01,270 --> 00:22:02,240
And I lack

479
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:04,370
the motivation to make a decision.

480
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:06,740
The first day I met you,

481
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,290
you had this spirit—

482
00:22:08,590 --> 00:22:09,880
something I don't have.

483
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,810
That's why I'm so attracted to you.

484
00:22:13,070 --> 00:22:14,680
When you first met me...

485
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:26,280
Actually, not long before that,

486
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:28,210
I was a hopeless person.

487
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:32,090
You were just in a desperate situation.

488
00:22:32,090 --> 00:22:33,480
If you were truly hopeless,

489
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:35,510
you wouldn't have been the way I saw you.

490
00:22:35,510 --> 00:22:36,240
Ms. Xiaolan.

491
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:39,350
Everyone faces difficulties

492
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:40,860
and hardships.

493
00:22:41,350 --> 00:22:42,030
But you

494
00:22:42,550 --> 00:22:43,310
showed me

495
00:22:43,310 --> 00:22:44,640
such vibrant vitality.

496
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,320
I'm not as good as you say,

497
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,350
but

498
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,890
I'm certainly not bad, either.

499
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:55,800
Take your time eating.

500
00:22:56,110 --> 00:22:57,970
I'm going to pursue my dreams now.

501
00:22:58,750 --> 00:22:59,480
Ms. Xiaolan.

502
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:00,900
Xiaolan...

503
00:23:05,070 --> 00:23:05,960
Wait for me!

504
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,730
I'll finish eating right away.

505
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,010
Wait for me a moment.

506
00:23:21,270 --> 00:23:22,530
Let me get you ten more.

507
00:23:22,790 --> 00:23:23,120
Good.

508
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:27,440
You bought twenty,

509
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:29,240
I'll give you some green onions.

510
00:23:29,270 --> 00:23:29,790
Okay.

511
00:23:29,790 --> 00:23:31,160
Fried duck eggs
with green onions are delicious.

512
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,200
Try it when you get home.

513
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,400
Alright, I'll try it.

514
00:23:33,550 --> 00:23:33,960
Here's the money.

515
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:34,790
Okay, thank you.

516
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:35,250
Thanks.

517
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,310
Popsicle!

518
00:23:39,030 --> 00:23:39,720
Popsicle!

519
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,020
Your lunchbox.

520
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:43,280
Thank you.

521
00:23:43,510 --> 00:23:45,240
The dumplings were delicious.

522
00:23:45,750 --> 00:23:47,790
Buy duck eggs and get scallions free?

523
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:49,310
You're really good at business.

524
00:23:49,310 --> 00:23:50,240
That's nothing,

525
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:51,920
just a basic sales strategy.

526
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:53,590
Sales strategy?

527
00:23:54,750 --> 00:23:55,950
You've studied this?

528
00:23:57,590 --> 00:23:58,920
I've read a bit about it.

529
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:01,750
Don't stand here.

530
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:02,440
You're blocking my business.

531
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:03,100
Move aside.

532
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:04,200
Do you want to buy duck eggs?

533
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:05,550
How much are these duck eggs?

534
00:24:05,550 --> 00:24:06,070
Take a look.

535
00:24:06,070 --> 00:24:07,130
Duck eggs for sale!

536
00:24:08,030 --> 00:24:09,640
The more you buy, the better deal you get.

537
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,900
Buy twenty
and you get green onions free.

538
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,310
Let me think about it.

539
00:24:13,310 --> 00:24:13,960
Alright.

540
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:18,350
If you're interested

541
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:19,280
in making money,

542
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,200
I can introduce you to some people

543
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,060
-I know—
-Stop.

544
00:24:22,270 --> 00:24:23,270
Yes, that's right.

545
00:24:23,270 --> 00:24:24,880
I am interested in making money,

546
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:26,440
but I don't need anyone's help.

547
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:27,440
I can do it myself.

548
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:30,100
Just by selling duck eggs?

549
00:24:32,270 --> 00:24:34,790
Selling duck eggs
was a form of primitive accumulation

550
00:24:34,790 --> 00:24:36,180
and also a way to test the waters.

551
00:24:36,180 --> 00:24:38,030
I'm not very familiar with this place.

552
00:24:38,030 --> 00:24:40,240
I need to research the market first

553
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:42,100
before changing the sales model.

554
00:24:42,310 --> 00:24:43,770
Once I have the equipment,

555
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:44,890
I can set up a stall

556
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:47,320
and sell egg pancakes and hamburgers here.

557
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:48,890
You're from the city, right?

558
00:24:48,890 --> 00:24:50,440
Then you must
have seen Western restaurants

559
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:51,480
and eaten hamburgers.

560
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,720
If

561
00:24:52,750 --> 00:24:54,200
I sell egg burgers here,

562
00:24:54,270 --> 00:24:55,870
would people here like them?

563
00:24:57,270 --> 00:24:58,790
I know all the words

564
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:00,110
you said,

565
00:25:01,030 --> 00:25:01,880
but when you put them together,

566
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:03,200
I don't understand what you mean.

567
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:05,590
P-primitive accumulation?

568
00:25:06,550 --> 00:25:07,480
Test the waters?

569
00:25:09,030 --> 00:25:10,880
I've never heard of these things.

570
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:11,440
Where did you learn

571
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:12,480
all of this?

572
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:14,510
I have eaten hamburgers before,

573
00:25:14,510 --> 00:25:16,270
but I've never heard of egg burgers.

574
00:25:16,270 --> 00:25:17,870
I'd actually like to try one.

575
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,110
Ms. Xiaolan,

576
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:22,030
you really are different from others.

577
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,720
Clothes for sale!

578
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:24,920
Clothes!

579
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:27,030
This fabric is really good.

580
00:25:27,030 --> 00:25:27,790
It's polyester fabric.

581
00:25:27,790 --> 00:25:28,510
What are you looking at?

582
00:25:28,510 --> 00:25:29,110
They are really cool.

583
00:25:29,110 --> 00:25:30,400
Do you want to buy clothes?

584
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,440
They look really nice.

585
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:32,350
No, not buy—

586
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:33,200
sell.

587
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:34,550
Selling clothes definitely

588
00:25:34,550 --> 00:25:36,720
makes more money
than selling farm products.

589
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:38,440
But I don't have enough capital now.

590
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:39,680
If I were selling them,

591
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:41,740
I'd definitely sell better than her.

592
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:47,880
Why haven't you left yet?

593
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:49,030
I want to buy...

594
00:25:49,030 --> 00:25:50,720
You heard what those thugs said yesterday,

595
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:51,550
didn't you?

596
00:25:52,510 --> 00:25:53,270
I might actually be

597
00:25:53,270 --> 00:25:55,000
different from what you think.

598
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:58,590
I don't judge people

599
00:25:58,590 --> 00:25:59,520
based on rumors.

600
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:01,480
I only believe what I see.

601
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:02,960
If I have doubts,

602
00:26:03,310 --> 00:26:04,240
I will research them myself,

603
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:07,100
and I won't just make assumptions
based on hearsay.

604
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:11,480
Unfortunately, there are too few people
like you.

605
00:26:11,550 --> 00:26:13,410
Some people don't just hate me...

606
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:15,250
They want to destroy me.

607
00:26:18,870 --> 00:26:20,980
Those "winged" rumors

608
00:26:21,440 --> 00:26:22,640
must come from

609
00:26:22,660 --> 00:26:24,190
my "golden phoenix" cousin

610
00:26:24,270 --> 00:26:25,330
and her boyfriend.

611
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:28,480
Can't even keep
one Xia Xiaolan under control.

612
00:26:29,070 --> 00:26:29,640
Ziyu.

613
00:26:35,270 --> 00:26:35,960
Jianhua.

614
00:26:37,070 --> 00:26:37,870
What's wrong?

615
00:26:38,550 --> 00:26:39,640
You look unhappy.

616
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:40,270
No,

617
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:41,410
I'm quite happy.

618
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:43,110
Let's go to the dining hall.

619
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:43,550
Okay.

620
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,250
Let's go.

621
00:26:47,150 --> 00:26:48,780
I don't care what tricks they're up to.

622
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:53,150
[State-Run Restaurant]

623
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:50,400
However,

624
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:52,270
being constantly followed by rumors

625
00:26:52,270 --> 00:26:53,330
is quite annoying.

626
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:55,170
Alright.

627
00:26:55,310 --> 00:26:56,720
If you need help,

628
00:26:56,750 --> 00:26:58,030
I can actually help you find...

629
00:26:58,030 --> 00:26:58,490
No need.

630
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:00,540
Actually, I won't be staying here

631
00:27:00,540 --> 00:27:01,580
for too long.

632
00:27:01,790 --> 00:27:03,550
I don't really mind these things.

633
00:27:03,550 --> 00:27:04,160
And even if

634
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:05,640
I really need to resolve it,

635
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:06,900
I can handle it myself.

636
00:27:07,590 --> 00:27:09,550
I don't want to owe you any more favors.

637
00:27:09,550 --> 00:27:10,550
There you two are!

638
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:11,480
Good.

639
00:27:11,830 --> 00:27:12,350
Sir,

640
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:14,640
I already had dumplings this morning.

641
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:15,440
No need to treat me to lunch.

642
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:16,240
That won't do.

643
00:27:16,310 --> 00:27:17,070
That's different.

644
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:18,800
I've already ordered the dishes.

645
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:20,000
We must show you our appreciation.

646
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:20,720
Come on in.

647
00:27:21,030 --> 00:27:21,510
Let's go.

648
00:27:21,510 --> 00:27:22,130
Well, thank you, sir.

649
00:27:22,130 --> 00:27:22,760
Come on.

650
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:30,240
All the dishes are here.

651
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:30,790
Sir.

652
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:33,070
Fish filets in hot chili oil,

653
00:27:33,070 --> 00:27:34,200
fish head with chopped chili,

654
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,750
fish ball soup, and fried fish fillets.

655
00:27:35,750 --> 00:27:37,070
It's one fish prepared in four ways!

656
00:27:37,070 --> 00:27:38,930
You've ordered a brilliant meal.

657
00:27:39,270 --> 00:27:41,030
This is... a black carp?

658
00:27:41,310 --> 00:27:43,110
It must be about 17 or 18 catties.

659
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,030
Mr. Zhou is

660
00:27:45,030 --> 00:27:46,360
really knowledgeable.

661
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:47,680
You can even tell

662
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:48,940
that it's a black carp.

663
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,240
Come on, eat up.

664
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:53,970
Here you are.

665
00:27:58,820 --> 00:27:59,780
Here, Xiaolan.

666
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:03,270
Use this one.

667
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:05,000
Eat up.

668
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:09,260
I'd like to toast you two

669
00:28:09,350 --> 00:28:10,750
for saving Xiaolan.

670
00:28:11,550 --> 00:28:12,550
Don't mention it.

671
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:14,180
You can call me Zhou Cheng.

672
00:28:14,350 --> 00:28:15,470
Or Cheng is fine, too.

673
00:28:15,470 --> 00:28:16,730
We'd like to toast you.

674
00:28:18,350 --> 00:28:19,790
Xiaolan and I hit it off when we

675
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:20,480
first met.

676
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,790
You're still so young.

677
00:28:26,790 --> 00:28:28,390
Don't speak so frivolously.

678
00:28:28,750 --> 00:28:31,350
What do you mean
you hit it off when you just met?

679
00:28:31,590 --> 00:28:32,680
We're treating you to this meal

680
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:34,220
to thank you for saving her life.

681
00:28:34,220 --> 00:28:35,050
That's all.

682
00:28:36,030 --> 00:28:37,440
You must mind your words.

683
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:39,880
I was being impertinent.

684
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,060
This is my apology.

685
00:28:45,530 --> 00:28:46,450
I'm so sorry

686
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:47,740
for the misunderstanding.

687
00:28:47,740 --> 00:28:48,730
I didn't mean anything else

688
00:28:48,730 --> 00:28:49,640
by saying that.

689
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,530
I just wanted to let you know

690
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:52,990
that I'm sincere

691
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:55,410
about being friends with Xiaolan.

692
00:29:05,030 --> 00:29:05,690
Zhou Cheng,

693
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:07,480
since you're being so honest,

694
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:08,940
I'll just cut to the chase.

695
00:29:09,270 --> 00:29:10,530
I admit you're not bad.

696
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:11,890
But right now,

697
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:13,350
I don't have time for this.

698
00:29:13,350 --> 00:29:15,280
I have more important things to do.

699
00:29:18,110 --> 00:29:19,640
I understand what you mean.

700
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:21,020
We've just met.

701
00:29:21,790 --> 00:29:22,850
I'm not rushing it.

702
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:25,350
And you don't need
to feel pressured, either.

703
00:29:25,350 --> 00:29:26,270
Let's interact

704
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:27,350
normally,

705
00:29:27,350 --> 00:29:28,410
just like friends.

706
00:29:29,270 --> 00:29:30,000
Try the fish.

707
00:29:31,690 --> 00:29:32,340
Have some fish, sir.

708
00:29:32,340 --> 00:29:33,470
Good that you got it.

709
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:36,680
I have to admit

710
00:29:37,030 --> 00:29:38,760
that under any circumstances,

711
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,550
this kind of youthful enthusiasm is

712
00:29:40,550 --> 00:29:41,550
always touching.

713
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,480
But touching as it may be,

714
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:46,560
this isn't my life after all.

715
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:47,830
Sooner or later, I'll return

716
00:29:47,830 --> 00:29:49,030
to the world I'm from.

717
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:51,440
Why form an additional attachment?

718
00:30:09,230 --> 00:30:10,510
Hey, man.

719
00:30:10,750 --> 00:30:11,480
We're the ones

720
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,140
who said to treat you to a meal.

721
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,730
Why did you pay the bill?

722
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:17,170
It doesn't matter who paid.

723
00:30:17,350 --> 00:30:17,880
The point is

724
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:19,480
that we all enjoyed the meal.

725
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:23,240
Are you two

726
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:24,350
going anywhere else?

727
00:30:24,350 --> 00:30:25,550
We can give you a ride.

728
00:30:25,670 --> 00:30:26,300
Don't bother.

729
00:30:26,300 --> 00:30:27,640
We've taken up your whole day already.

730
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:28,750
Just go ahead with your business.

731
00:30:28,750 --> 00:30:29,550
We'll be fine.

732
00:30:32,430 --> 00:30:32,960
Alright.

733
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:34,400
Take care on your way.

734
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:36,290
We'll be staying here for two more days.

735
00:30:36,290 --> 00:30:37,690
If you come into town for anything,

736
00:30:37,690 --> 00:30:39,550
you can find us at the guesthouse.

737
00:30:41,070 --> 00:30:41,680
Well,

738
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,120
we'll take our leave.

739
00:30:59,440 --> 00:30:59,880
Cheng,

740
00:31:00,310 --> 00:31:02,200
you didn't go to the police station today.

741
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:04,240
What those three thugs said is so nasty

742
00:31:04,240 --> 00:31:05,310
that I don't even want to repeat it.

743
00:31:05,310 --> 00:31:06,770
Then just don't repeat it.

744
00:31:07,990 --> 00:31:08,400
Wei.

745
00:31:09,590 --> 00:31:11,050
Do you think I'm handsome?

746
00:31:11,590 --> 00:31:12,440
Yes, of course!

747
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:13,350
Back in the compound when we were kids,

748
00:31:13,350 --> 00:31:14,950
all the girls were after you.

749
00:31:14,980 --> 00:31:15,780
Then am I rich?

750
00:31:17,100 --> 00:31:18,960
Since I'm both handsome and rich,

751
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:21,480
and I've openly expressed
my admiration for her,

752
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:22,440
if she were really

753
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,110
as terrible

754
00:31:23,110 --> 00:31:24,170
as that rogue said,

755
00:31:24,350 --> 00:31:25,700
why would she turn down someone

756
00:31:25,700 --> 00:31:27,500
with such good conditions as me?

757
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:32,370
She'll be your sister-in-law one day.

758
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:33,340
Let's go

759
00:31:33,700 --> 00:31:34,500
do something.

760
00:31:35,550 --> 00:31:37,750
Weren't we going back
to rest at the guesthouse?

761
00:31:37,750 --> 00:31:39,240
These two must be

762
00:31:39,590 --> 00:31:40,790
smugglers

763
00:31:41,550 --> 00:31:42,950
doing illegal business.

764
00:31:43,730 --> 00:31:44,650
They might

765
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:46,080
lose everything one day.

766
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:47,030
You can't just be fooled

767
00:31:47,030 --> 00:31:48,630
by this man's handsome looks

768
00:31:48,750 --> 00:31:50,480
and sweet talk.

769
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:53,730
How do you know all this?

770
00:31:54,590 --> 00:31:56,110
Aren't you a mason?

771
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:59,200
How do you know so much about smuggling?

772
00:32:01,310 --> 00:32:02,680
Because I'm smart.

773
00:32:05,550 --> 00:32:07,400
Let's s-stop talking about those two.

774
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:09,400
Let's talk about those three thugs.

775
00:32:09,660 --> 00:32:11,270
They're now insisting

776
00:32:11,310 --> 00:32:12,830
that they only went to hurt you

777
00:32:12,830 --> 00:32:13,960
after hearing those rumors.

778
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:15,750
They'll definitely get a heavy sentence.

779
00:32:15,750 --> 00:32:17,000
At your age,

780
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:18,790
reputation matters so much.

781
00:32:18,790 --> 00:32:19,240
These days...

782
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:21,240
P-Please don't do anything for now.

783
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:22,680
Let me think about it.

784
00:32:23,260 --> 00:32:23,880
Hello, excuse me.

785
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:24,880
I'd like to ask about someone.

786
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:26,270
Do you know Zhang Erlai?

787
00:32:27,030 --> 00:32:28,370
He's just a hideous scoundrel.

788
00:32:28,370 --> 00:32:28,920
He's messed

789
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:29,880
with many young girls

790
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:31,030
from several villages around here.

791
00:32:31,030 --> 00:32:31,750
Thank you, ma'am.

792
00:32:31,750 --> 00:32:32,110
Sir,

793
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,240
could I ask you about someone?

794
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:34,640
Do you know Zhang Erlai?

795
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:36,640
I'm busy and don't have time for you.

796
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:42,000
Cheng,

797
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:43,550
see?

798
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,480
We've been hearing all day about how she

799
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,640
failed to seduce her cousin's husband

800
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:47,720
and turned to mess

801
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:48,270
with that rascal.

802
00:32:48,270 --> 00:32:48,870
Screw you.

803
00:32:50,310 --> 00:32:51,830
Look, even if I believe

804
00:32:51,830 --> 00:32:53,160
that Xia Xiaolan isn't
that kind of person,

805
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:54,690
everyone here is saying it.

806
00:32:54,790 --> 00:32:55,400
Getting mixed up with her

807
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,920
will surely bring you endless trouble.

808
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:57,590
First of all,

809
00:32:57,590 --> 00:32:59,440
your family won't easily accept her.

810
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:00,100
Look at you.

811
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,040
You saved her,

812
00:33:01,350 --> 00:33:02,310
confessed your love in public,

813
00:33:02,310 --> 00:33:03,640
and showed off your wealth.

814
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:04,110
But look at her.

815
00:33:04,110 --> 00:33:05,270
She's not interested at all.

816
00:33:05,270 --> 00:33:07,130
Just pack up and come home with me.

817
00:33:07,350 --> 00:33:08,280
I'm not leaving.

818
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:09,790
Let's go

819
00:33:09,850 --> 00:33:10,680
to Shipozi Village

820
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:11,540
they mentioned

821
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:13,160
and meet Zhang Erlai.

822
00:33:15,460 --> 00:33:17,520
You've been bewitched by that woman.

823
00:33:32,590 --> 00:33:33,520
This alarm clock

824
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:35,200
rings whenever

825
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:36,350
you want it to.

826
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:56,790
Xiaolan,

827
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:59,100
your alarm clock rings so loudly.

828
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:00,940
Auntie,

829
00:34:01,110 --> 00:34:02,070
this is the money I earned

830
00:34:02,070 --> 00:34:03,210
selling duck eggs in the past few days.

831
00:34:03,210 --> 00:34:03,830
Please take it

832
00:34:03,830 --> 00:34:05,030
for our food expense.

833
00:34:05,590 --> 00:34:06,200
Well...

834
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:06,660
Take it.

835
00:34:07,160 --> 00:34:07,490
Oh...

836
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:08,800
What's this for?

837
00:34:09,510 --> 00:34:11,110
You don't need to do this
while living at your uncle's house.

838
00:34:11,110 --> 00:34:11,880
We don't need your money.

839
00:34:11,880 --> 00:34:12,480
That's right.

840
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:13,670
I know you don't need it,

841
00:34:13,670 --> 00:34:15,469
but if you don't take this money,

842
00:34:15,670 --> 00:34:16,440
I'd feel bad

843
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:17,840
staying here any longer.

844
00:34:18,110 --> 00:34:19,590
Look at this girl...

845
00:34:20,110 --> 00:34:20,969
How about this?

846
00:34:21,070 --> 00:34:21,760
Your auntie will

847
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:23,090
keep this money for you,

848
00:34:23,150 --> 00:34:24,590
and when you need it,

849
00:34:24,710 --> 00:34:25,760
she'll return it to you.

850
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:27,400
Yeah, good girl.

851
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,030
What's wrong?

852
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:36,110
Nothing.

853
00:34:36,590 --> 00:34:37,190
It's just

854
00:34:37,190 --> 00:34:39,050
that I didn't get many eggs today.

855
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:42,400
Anyone can tell your sadness
from your face.

856
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:43,730
What's really going on?

857
00:34:44,590 --> 00:34:45,650
The villagers said

858
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:47,460
duck eggs are profitable.

859
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,280
They want to sell them themselves

860
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,540
and can't give me many.

861
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:53,400
I should have told you earlier.

862
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:54,840
I actually expected this.

863
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:55,969
People always fight

864
00:34:56,110 --> 00:34:57,280
for jobs that pay well.

865
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:59,140
So what if we didn't get duck eggs?

866
00:35:03,590 --> 00:35:04,110
Fen?

867
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:07,290
What's wrong, Fen?

868
00:35:07,670 --> 00:35:08,710
Why are you crying?

869
00:35:08,710 --> 00:35:09,840
What are you crying for?

870
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:10,360
Fen,

871
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:11,280
don't cry.

872
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:12,920
They were talking

873
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:14,550
about Xiaolan.

874
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:16,360
What did they say?

875
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:17,360
What did they say?

876
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:19,810
They said she...

877
00:35:25,030 --> 00:35:26,280
Who's got nothing better to do

878
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:27,440
than gossip around here?

879
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,000
What are you doing?

880
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:29,110
Get your ass over here!

881
00:35:29,110 --> 00:35:31,010
I'll rip that tongue
right out of your big mouth!

882
00:35:31,010 --> 00:35:31,480
That's enough.

883
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:32,410
How despicable,

884
00:35:32,510 --> 00:35:34,150
talking rubbish about our innocent girl!

885
00:35:34,150 --> 00:35:35,410
You shameless people!

886
00:35:35,590 --> 00:35:36,670
Enough, Fengmei. Stop it...

887
00:35:36,670 --> 00:35:37,400
You think our family has no one

888
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:38,110
to stand up for her?

889
00:35:38,110 --> 00:35:38,960
Stop shouting!

890
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:40,220
Xiaolan is still here!

891
00:35:42,110 --> 00:35:43,310
And you, stop crying.

892
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:43,880
Your tears

893
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:44,960
won't solve anything!

894
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:45,630
Those damn bastards are

895
00:35:45,630 --> 00:35:47,830
spreading rumors and causing trouble.

896
00:35:48,030 --> 00:35:48,630
I know

897
00:35:49,230 --> 00:35:50,760
it must be that Zhang Erlai!

898
00:35:51,240 --> 00:35:52,080
Zhang Erlai is

899
00:35:52,110 --> 00:35:53,110
a filthy hooligan,

900
00:35:53,110 --> 00:35:53,840
a scoundrel!

901
00:35:56,030 --> 00:35:58,360
I'm not the Xia Xiaolan they gossip about.

902
00:35:58,710 --> 00:36:00,240
These things can't hurt me.

903
00:36:01,230 --> 00:36:02,590
But they can hurt them,

904
00:36:03,550 --> 00:36:04,950
my unfamiliar "family."

905
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:06,660
Don't let me see you!

906
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:07,230
I'll beat you

907
00:36:07,230 --> 00:36:08,760
every single time I see you!

908
00:36:08,960 --> 00:36:10,480
What they're saying isn't true.

909
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:11,940
Xiaolan, you are the best.

910
00:36:14,970 --> 00:36:16,000
See? He failed to get what he wanted,

911
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:17,030
so he's spreading rumors here!

912
00:36:17,030 --> 00:36:17,630
All right,

913
00:36:18,070 --> 00:36:18,800
stop crying.

914
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:23,090
Zhang Erlai,

915
00:36:23,590 --> 00:36:24,070
right?

916
00:36:32,710 --> 00:36:34,000
Zhang Erlai is

917
00:36:34,190 --> 00:36:36,070
always getting handsy.

918
00:36:36,220 --> 00:36:37,610
The women in Shipozi Village

919
00:36:37,610 --> 00:36:38,500
all avoid him.

920
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:42,670
It's improper for me
to confront him directly.

921
00:36:42,670 --> 00:36:44,070
Could you help me find out

922
00:36:44,360 --> 00:36:46,000
if he has any hobbies

923
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:47,810
or places he likes to go?

924
00:36:49,110 --> 00:36:50,310
You want to catch him?

925
00:36:53,030 --> 00:36:54,830
Words alone aren't solid proof.

926
00:36:55,230 --> 00:36:56,760
We must catch him in the act.

927
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:57,920
Someone like him will strike

928
00:36:57,920 --> 00:36:59,520
whenever he gets the chance.

929
00:37:02,190 --> 00:37:03,510
I've already spoken with people

930
00:37:03,510 --> 00:37:04,800
in his village and told them

931
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:06,260
to keep an eye on him for me.

932
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:08,880
Ma'am.

933
00:37:09,130 --> 00:37:09,730
Oh, right,

934
00:37:09,970 --> 00:37:10,960
they said recently,

935
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:11,800
someone else was also

936
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:13,260
asking about Zhang Erlai.

937
00:37:13,670 --> 00:37:16,030
This guy seems to have offended
quite a few people.

938
00:37:16,030 --> 00:37:17,490
Everyone wants to get him.

939
00:37:17,590 --> 00:37:18,390
Someone else?

940
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:20,880
Looks like Zhang Erlai

941
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:21,880
lives up to his name.

942
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:22,940
He's no good at all.

943
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:24,920
Hello, sir.

944
00:37:25,250 --> 00:37:26,130
Excuse me,

945
00:37:26,150 --> 00:37:27,550
do you know Zhang Erlai?

946
00:37:29,550 --> 00:37:30,080
Get lost!

947
00:37:31,910 --> 00:37:32,400
Don't run!

948
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,070
Kids, come here.

949
00:37:33,070 --> 00:37:33,840
I must catch him.

950
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:35,190
I have a question for you.

951
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:35,880
If you

952
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:36,880
know anything,

953
00:37:37,070 --> 00:37:38,760
you'll get a candy.

954
00:37:39,030 --> 00:37:40,400
Okay! Me!

955
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:42,150
Who knows Zhang Erlai?

956
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:43,280
I know! I know him.

957
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:45,510
Xiaoling's sister stays at home all day,

958
00:37:45,510 --> 00:37:46,710
cursing Zhang Erlai.

959
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:47,250
Yeah.

960
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:47,630
Dan'er,

961
00:37:47,630 --> 00:37:48,480
didn't he once

962
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:49,480
grope your sister, too?

963
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:50,510
He groped your sister!

964
00:37:50,510 --> 00:37:51,570
It was your sister!

965
00:38:39,330 --> 00:38:40,670
[To Xia Xiaolan]

966
00:38:52,980 --> 00:38:55,500
[See you at the usual spot. From Jianhua.]

967
00:39:09,150 --> 00:39:11,360
The handwriting is completely different.

968
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,400
She fell

969
00:39:12,400 --> 00:39:13,730
for such a clumsy trick.

970
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:15,360
What a silly girl.

971
00:39:20,380 --> 00:39:21,580
What's wrong, Cheng?

972
00:39:21,630 --> 00:39:23,490
This Zhang Erlai has gone too far.

973
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:25,760
Xia Xiaolan must have been wronged.

974
00:39:26,480 --> 00:39:27,400
Visit two more houses

975
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:28,380
and send all this evidence

976
00:39:28,380 --> 00:39:29,640
to the police station.

977
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:32,030
W-Where are you going?

978
00:39:32,030 --> 00:39:33,490
Aren't you coming with me?

979
00:39:33,510 --> 00:39:34,920
I'm going to help your sister-in-law

980
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:36,030
sell duck eggs.

981
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:39,760
Cheng!

982
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:42,080
Xiaolan!

983
00:39:43,360 --> 00:39:44,630
Are you still buying duck eggs?

984
00:39:44,630 --> 00:39:45,070
Yes.

985
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,860
I have twelve here.

986
00:39:47,150 --> 00:39:47,960
I have eight.

987
00:39:48,110 --> 00:39:49,370
I'll give you 70 cents.

988
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:50,150
And 50 cents for you.

989
00:39:50,150 --> 00:39:50,920
Okay.

990
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:51,400
Put them in here.

991
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:52,230
I'll get you money.

992
00:39:52,230 --> 00:39:52,560
Okay.

993
00:39:52,920 --> 00:39:53,980
I'll put them here.

994
00:39:58,150 --> 00:39:59,030
Here's yours.

995
00:40:00,030 --> 00:40:00,630
Thank you.

996
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:02,440
And yours.

997
00:40:02,550 --> 00:40:04,030
Okay, thanks.

998
00:40:04,630 --> 00:40:05,920
Are these duck eggs for sale?

999
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:06,320
Yes.

1000
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:09,440
Xiaolan,

1001
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:10,640
good morning.

1002
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:11,890
Why are you here?

1003
00:40:12,670 --> 00:40:14,870
I still have some unfinished business.

1004
00:40:17,710 --> 00:40:19,630
Why so few duck eggs today?

1005
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:21,670
The villagers

1006
00:40:21,670 --> 00:40:23,110
heard that selling duck eggs makes money,

1007
00:40:23,110 --> 00:40:24,790
so few would sell them to me now.

1008
00:40:24,790 --> 00:40:26,230
They all want to make money themselves.

1009
00:40:26,230 --> 00:40:27,280
But it doesn't matter.

1010
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:28,440
I don't plan

1011
00:40:28,440 --> 00:40:30,240
to stay in this business anyway.

1012
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,160
What will you do next?

1013
00:40:32,550 --> 00:40:33,480
Next?

1014
00:40:34,030 --> 00:40:35,690
I haven't thought about that.

1015
00:40:36,590 --> 00:40:38,280
Since there's no business today anyway,

1016
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:38,740
come on,

1017
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:40,860
I'll show you some rural scenery.

1018
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:43,480
Handle them gently.

1019
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:44,440
You'll have to pay if they break.

1020
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:44,840
Okay.

1021
00:40:59,700 --> 00:41:01,630
That's the one from Dahe Village, right?

1022
00:41:01,630 --> 00:41:02,630
I think so.

1023
00:41:03,230 --> 00:41:04,070
That's her.

1024
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:06,590
-Why did she get mixed up with Zhang Erlai?
-That's how rumors spread.

1025
00:41:06,590 --> 00:41:07,550
Exactly.

1026
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:09,800
It's the same in the city.

1027
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:10,590
Some things

1028
00:41:10,590 --> 00:41:12,400
get distorted when passed around.

1029
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:14,260
It's hard to keep everyone quiet.

1030
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:18,340
You scoundrel!

1031
00:41:18,590 --> 00:41:19,920
You have nowhere to escape!

1032
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:21,250
Isn't that Zhang Erlai?

1033
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:22,090
Zhang Erlai!

1034
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:23,280
Why are you here?

1035
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:25,480
You harass young girls
in the village every day!

1036
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:26,880
You disgusting pervert!

1037
00:41:27,110 --> 00:41:28,640
Why is your uncle here, too?

1038
00:41:29,230 --> 00:41:30,230
Since we're here,

1039
00:41:30,510 --> 00:41:31,710
let's watch the show.

1040
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:32,450
Zhang Erlai,

1041
00:41:32,750 --> 00:41:33,480
you bullied Xia Xiaolan

1042
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:35,280
from Dahe Village the other day.

1043
00:41:35,390 --> 00:41:36,630
This person should've called the police

1044
00:41:36,630 --> 00:41:37,840
and sent you to the police station!

1045
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:38,510
Yes, that's right.

1046
00:41:38,510 --> 00:41:39,920
Call the police to catch him.

1047
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:41,110
Don't talk nonsense.

1048
00:41:41,110 --> 00:41:42,880
There's nothing
between Xia Xiaolan and me.

1049
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:43,760
If you keep making things up,

1050
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:45,440
I'll tell the police to arrest you!

1051
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:47,040
Did you see it with your eyes?

1052
00:41:47,150 --> 00:41:48,750
Dare you come to confront me?

1053
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:50,190
He's still denying it!

1054
00:41:50,190 --> 00:41:50,840
He thinks he's right!

1055
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:53,640
-That's horrendous!
-Let me confront you myself.

1056
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:55,530
Zhang Erlai,

1057
00:41:56,550 --> 00:41:57,610
do you remember me?

1058
00:41:58,480 --> 00:41:59,400
Xia Xiaolan?

1059
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:00,760
Repeat what you

1060
00:42:00,760 --> 00:42:01,440
just said.

1061
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:02,440
I...

1062
00:42:02,770 --> 00:42:04,090
What did I say?

1063
00:42:04,150 --> 00:42:04,670
Speak!

1064
00:42:05,150 --> 00:42:06,760
Weren't you quite talkative just now?

1065
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:07,490
Say it again!

1066
00:42:08,550 --> 00:42:10,080
Be it in the past or present,

1067
00:42:10,630 --> 00:42:11,800
when misunderstood

1068
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:12,720
or slandered,

1069
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:14,670
many people only choose to run away.

1070
00:42:14,670 --> 00:42:16,110
But when you hide from rumors,

1071
00:42:16,110 --> 00:42:17,910
the rumors will chase after you.

1072
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,890
There's only one way to end rumors.

1073
00:42:20,260 --> 00:42:20,810
And that is

1074
00:42:20,810 --> 00:42:22,270
to confront them head-on.

1075
00:42:23,030 --> 00:42:24,030
Fine, I'll speak!

1076
00:42:24,590 --> 00:42:26,230
I'm not that kind of perverted person.

1077
00:42:26,230 --> 00:42:28,200
And I've never done that filthy thing!

1078
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:29,450
Oh... How shameless!

1079
00:42:29,480 --> 00:42:30,440
Look how nervous he appears!

1080
00:42:30,440 --> 00:42:31,300
Of course he's nervous.

1081
00:42:31,300 --> 00:42:32,560
He's obviously lying.

1082
00:42:32,590 --> 00:42:33,480
Zhang Erlai and I

1083
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:35,230
have met only three times in total.

1084
00:42:35,230 --> 00:42:36,360
The first two times,

1085
00:42:36,810 --> 00:42:38,330
you verbally flirted

1086
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:39,360
and got handsy with me.

1087
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:40,670
I scolded you and drove you away.

1088
00:42:40,670 --> 00:42:41,360
Later, I don't know

1089
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:42,710
who left you a note,

1090
00:42:42,840 --> 00:42:44,440
claiming that I fell for you.

1091
00:42:45,110 --> 00:42:46,190
Who'd possibly

1092
00:42:46,260 --> 00:42:47,400
fall for someone like him?

1093
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:47,930
Exactly!

1094
00:42:48,300 --> 00:42:50,230
Someone really did leave me a note.

1095
00:42:50,510 --> 00:42:51,240
Zhang Erlai!

1096
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:52,760
That doesn't make any sense.

1097
00:42:52,760 --> 00:42:53,670
You just believed

1098
00:42:53,670 --> 00:42:54,630
some random note?

1099
00:42:54,630 --> 00:42:55,360
That girl is

1100
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:56,360
so capable and competent.

1101
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:57,590
She'd have to be blind to like you.

1102
00:42:57,590 --> 00:42:58,190
Exactly.

1103
00:42:58,670 --> 00:42:59,800
I was just thinking,

1104
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:00,710
"What if it's true?"

1105
00:43:00,710 --> 00:43:01,550
Seriously?

1106
00:43:01,550 --> 00:43:02,320
Who gave you that note?

1107
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:03,360
How ridiculous! Look at yourself.

1108
00:43:03,360 --> 00:43:03,960
So hilarious.

1109
00:43:03,960 --> 00:43:05,400
How would I know who left me that?

1110
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:06,590
When I got home,

1111
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:08,110
the note was right under my door.

1112
00:43:08,110 --> 00:43:09,590
I received a similar note,

1113
00:43:10,550 --> 00:43:11,960
but it wasn't about you.

1114
00:43:12,550 --> 00:43:13,610
After meeting you,

1115
00:43:13,800 --> 00:43:15,930
I immediately made my position clear.

1116
00:43:16,070 --> 00:43:17,360
I also showed you the note.

1117
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:18,150
You knew perfectly well

1118
00:43:18,150 --> 00:43:19,360
that I was tricked into coming.

1119
00:43:19,360 --> 00:43:21,160
Yet you still got handsy with me.

1120
00:43:21,630 --> 00:43:22,800
I tried everything to get rid of you,

1121
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:24,030
and you, embarrassed and furious,

1122
00:43:24,030 --> 00:43:24,960
spread rumors everywhere,

1123
00:43:24,960 --> 00:43:26,490
saying that we were dating.

1124
00:43:26,630 --> 00:43:27,590
How can a young woman like you

1125
00:43:27,590 --> 00:43:28,520
be so shameless?

1126
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:29,960
We're in front of so many people.

1127
00:43:29,960 --> 00:43:30,630
How can you eagerly talk about

1128
00:43:30,630 --> 00:43:31,510
such embarrassing things?

1129
00:43:31,510 --> 00:43:33,110
Why should I be embarrassed?

1130
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:34,550
If I didn't speak up,

1131
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:35,820
people might think

1132
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:37,440
I was admitting it silently out of shame.

1133
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:38,230
Should I let

1134
00:43:38,230 --> 00:43:39,150
a rogue like you

1135
00:43:39,380 --> 00:43:39,920
and all those

1136
00:43:39,920 --> 00:43:41,000
malicious rumors

1137
00:43:41,030 --> 00:43:42,000
belittle me?

1138
00:43:42,110 --> 00:43:42,710
-You're right!
-Exactly.

1139
00:43:42,710 --> 00:43:44,000
Should I let someone like you,

1140
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:45,400
who spreads rumors everywhere,

1141
00:43:45,400 --> 00:43:46,510
continue doing evil,

1142
00:43:46,510 --> 00:43:47,110
and let someone like me,

1143
00:43:47,110 --> 00:43:48,320
a completely innocent victim,

1144
00:43:48,320 --> 00:43:49,680
live in shame and fear?

1145
00:43:50,110 --> 00:43:50,840
On what grounds?
